{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644259","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644259"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:04:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18038"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18038","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18038"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.35,0.04,0.15,0.31]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10752"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74144"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10752","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10752"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18038"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59635"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8407"},{"type":"tags","id":"10202"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25085"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25088"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74144"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about bone histology is correct?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Compact bone is found along stress lines","Blood supply for trabecular bone comes from bone marrow","Trabecular bone is found at the outer surface of bone","Trabecular bone does not contain osteocytes","In trabecular bone, cells are arranged in lamellae"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlood supply for trabecular bone comes from bone marrow\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. Trabecular bone, also known as spongy bone, is located within the interior of bones and is surrounded by bone marrow, which provides its blood supply.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETrabecular bone is found at the outer surface of bone\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Trabecular bone is found inside bones, particularly at the ends of long bones and within the vertebrae, not at the outer surface.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIn trabecular bone, cells are arranged in lamellae\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While trabecular bone does have a lamellar structure, it is less organized than the lamellae found in compact bone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECompact bone is found along stress lines\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Compact bone forms the dense outer layer of bone, providing support and strength, but it is not specifically aligned along stress lines like trabecular bone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETrabecular bone does not contain osteocytes\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Trabecular bone contains osteocytes, which are housed in lacunae within the bone matrix, similar to compact bone.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Trabecular bone, also known as spongy bone, located near the end of long bones and within vertebral interiors.","Trabecular bone contains osteocytes within its structure, similar to compact bone.","The blood supply for trabecular bone comes from the bone marrow, which is located within the trabecular spaces."],"references":["Gartner, L. P. (2020). Textbook of histology e-book: Textbook of histology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Baig MA, Bacha D. Histology, Bone. 2023 May 1. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMI